1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. Nc3 c6 4. Bc4 d6 5. Qf3 { The deferred Monkey's bum! } 5... e6 6. Nge2 { [%cal Gd6d5] } 6... b5 (6... d5 7. Bd3 Nd7 { [%csl Ge3][%cal Gc2c4] }) 7. Bb3 a5 8. a3 { [%cal Gb5b4,Ga3b4,Ga1a8] } (8. a4?! b4) 8... Ba6 { [%cal Gd4d5] } 9. d5 cxd5 10. exd5 e5 11. Ne4 { [%cal Gh7h6] } 11... Qc7? { We have the go-ahead to attack as white because black is completely paralyzed on the kingside. Any knight developing move will allow Nf6+ Bxf6 Qxf6 in which 0-0 loses to Bh6 and any rook move ensures that black is never castling to safety. Because we're ahead in development and will continue to be ahead in development, we can go ahead and blast open the center. } { [%csl Gg8][%cal Gc2c4,Gb3d5] } (11... h6 { The improvement Shirov tried against Anand 1 year later. It too didn't work out for him, although computer thinks "equal" }) 12. c4! { [%cal Gb3a4,Ga4e8] } 12... bxc4 13. Ba4+ Nd7 14. N2c3 { [%csl Ga6] } 14... Ke7?? { A blunder, but a reasonable one. Black is desperately trying to play Nf6 } (14... h6! 15. Nxd6+ Qxd6 16. Ne4 Qxd5 17. Be3 Bb7 18. Rd1 Qxe4 19. Rxd7 Nf6 20. Rxb7+ Kf8 21. Qxe4 Nxe4 22. O-O $18 { [%csl Gb7] }) 15. Nxd6 { [%cal Gf3f7,Gd6f7] } 15... Qxd6 (15... Kxd6 16. Ne4+ { [%cal Gd6e7,Gd5d6] } 16... Ke7 (16... Kxd5 17. Qxf7+ Kxe4 18. Bc2+ Kd4 19. Be3#) 17. d6+) 16. Ne4 { [%cal Gd5d6] } 16... Qxd5 17. Bg5+ Ndf6 (17... Ngf6 18. Bxd7 Qxd7 19. Nxf6 $18 { [%csl Gd8,Ge8,Gf8][%cal Gg7f6,Gf3f6,Gf6h8] }) (17... f6 18. Rd1 Qe6 (18... Qxd1+ 19. Qxd1 { [%csl Gd6,Gd7][%cal Gd1d7,Ga4d7,Gd1d6] }) (18... Bb7 19. Rxd5 Bxd5 20. Qd1! { [%cal Gd1d7] } 20... Nb6 21. Be3 Bxe4 22. Bxb6 { [%csl Gd8,Gd7][%cal Gd1d7] }) 19. Rxd7+ $18) (17... Kf8 18. Rd1 { [%csl Gd5,Gd7][%cal Gd1d7] }) 18. Rd1 Qb7 (18... Qxd1+ 19. Qxd1 (19. Bxd1 { [%csl Gf6] }) 19... Rd8 20. Qf3 { [%csl Gf6] }) 19. Rd7+ Qxd7 20. Bxd7 h6 21. Qd1 { 1-0 White wins. } { [%cal Gd1d6] } 21... hxg5 22. Qd6+ Kd8 23. Bb5+ Kc8 { [%cal Ge4d6] } 24. Qc6+ Kd8 (24... Kb8 25. Qb6+ Bb7 26. Nd6 { [%cal Gb6b7] } 26... Ra7 27. Qd8+ Bc8 28. Qxc8#) 25. Qb6+ Kc8 26. Nd6# 1-0


